All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbstractTaskLog
The AbstractTaskLog class is an abstract class at the top of the hierarchy for lists of logged tasks.
AllTasksLog
Class that extends the AbstractTaskLog and overrides behavior for setting the log's name
CategoryLog
CategoryLog represents a log for tasks within a specific category.
ILogList<E>
Interface for logged items.
ISortedList<E>
Interface for a list that keeps objects in sorted order as defined by the Comparable interface.
LogList<E>
LogList implements a custom array-based list to store task elements.
Project
Contains an ISrotedList of CategoryLog s, the AllTasksLog, and operations to manipulate these logs.
ProjectReader
ProjectReader is responsible for reading project files that contain project information, including categories and tasks.
ProjectWriter
The ProjectWriter is responsible for writing project data to specified files.
SortedList<E>
The SortedList class implements a sorted linked list that maintains category elements in a sorted order.
Task
The Task Class contains the information about each individual task includiing the taskTitle, taskDuration, and taskDetails.
WolfTrackerGUI
Container for the Wolf Tracker project that provides the user the ability to interact with projects and logged tasks.
